This paper is primarily focused on improving information retrieval (IR) tasks using word embeddings, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques like word2vec and GloVe, which are commonly used in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a new set of word embeddings models that include affect information, which could be considered as a machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) technique. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on a dataset, which involves experimentation and evaluation, and could be categorized under Computer Communications (cs.CC).
